//9. How do you get the first character of a string in Scala? The last character?

Resolution Exercice-9

val s = "String"                            // s : String = String
  s.head                                    // res0: Char = S
  s. s(0)                                      // res1: Char = S


  s.last                                    // res2: Char = g
  s(s.length - 1)                           // res3: Char = g
